CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 14, 1954, pg. 3 reads: "At Omegas' Picnic - Pittsburgh's chapters of Omega Psi Phi Fraternity held their annual picnic at North Park Lodge Tuesday afternoon and evening...Some of the Omegas who attended are shown in the picture on the far right. They are, first row: Melvin Scott, Andrew Cole and Charles Watkins, Basileus.  Second row: Frank Lavelle, Earl Brooks, co-social chairman; Atty. Warren Watson, Ronnie Pittman, Harry Conrad and Dr. J.D. Avent Jr., Vice Basileus.  Back row: Edmund Davis, George Bell and Ted Jamison.  A few of the others present but not on the picture were Tom Hampton, Winstead Adams, Dr. Stockton, Richard Smith and David Cook. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Omega Psi Phi fraternity members, first row from left: Melvin Scott, Andrew Cole, and Charles Watkins; second row: Frank Lavelle, Earl Brooks, Atty. Warren Watson, Ronnie Pittman, Harry Conrad, and Dr. J. D. Avent Jr.: back row: Edmund Davis, George Bell, and Ted Jamison, gathered at North Park Lodge for annual picnic.
